<br>
Personally, I don't see the big deal about hell levels pre-50 as they are always waaaaaay over-exaggerated. People think they last longer because they become discouraged and start alts or a million other things that stop the XP from flowing.<br>
<br>
The XP gain up to level 10 acceleration thing I'm not sold on. FIrst of all, it wasn't slow to begin with. Why must it be much faster? Because DAoC is faster? BS. When I was a true n00b, I could care less how slow I levelled pre-10. In fact, I didn't KNOW it was slow at all. Things don't slow down at all for a goo dmany levels, so I don't see the point.<br>
<br>
Starting with all of your gear pre-10 is a bad idea. The quicker a n00b learns the value of a CR and how to accomplish it the better. All I wish is that VI would eliminate the corpse-poof concept. Instead, at the end of 7 RL days, someone's corpse should appear at their current bind point. Their's still a significant penalty for not recovering a corpse.<br>
<br>
The treatment of n00bs reminds me of a Friends episode. Chandler wants to give Joey some dough, so he invents a card game as they go, where Joey continually wins money. The rules are ridiculous and completely contrived. Eventually Joey gets the money, but he then plays Ross in the game and loses it all by the same stupid rules invented to help him.<br>
<br>
What's this mean? N00bs are going to be &quot;weaker&quot; because they have it easier. Then again, perhaps they'll have a little more fun, so it just MIGHT balance out.<br>
<br>
I'm glad to see the book going, however, I'm not certain that casters should be able to see their surroundings either. Staring at the book is part of balancing the awesome powers of casters. Casters get a lot of neat toys like the ability to bind anywhere, gate, nice damage, etc.<br>
<br>
I suggest casters look at something more interesting, but not the game world. Psychadelic vortex! Whoohoo!<br>
<br>
I can't agree with the idea that this is socialism however. This doesn't eliminate competiton at all. N00bs still have to work for their supper.  <p><img border="0" src="http://www.mindspring.com/~smullen/images/sigtmp.jpg" width="250" height="128"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ustalkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stalkin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#333333>(3/18/02 2:46:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=469.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/stalkinpowers/stalkstfu.jpg WIDTH=145 HEIGHT=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Horrible Change for the Game of EQ</span><hr size=1> First off hell levels are not really being removed, the exp it takes to level from 1-50 now will be the same as after they fix the hell levels.  So there may be no hell levels but it will take just a tad bit longer to level every other level.<br>
